This paper is about social influence maximization, which is a topic in social network analysis and falls under the category of computational social science (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the use of various optimization techniques and algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of economic utilities, which could place it in the category of microeconomics and game theory (cs.MA) or computational economics (cs.CE).
